# 3. 星よりベース

Ichika: The observatory?
Saki: Yeah! Let's all go next Saturday! You normally don't get to go inside, you know!
Honami: Oh, I heard about it too! It's usually closed to the public.
Honami: They're doing an open lecture about stars, so I was thinking about going myself!
Saki: I expect no less from you, Honami, our resident star expert!
Honami: You're exaggerating... Besides, that place is quite famous.
Luka: That's very interesting. A place where you can see the stars and learn about them.
Miku: I can imagine that knowing more about stars makes gazing at them even more enjoyable.
Saki: Right?
Shiho: You don't need to go to an observatory to see the stars. They even look prettier here.
Saki: Th-That's a true... But I thought it'd be nice if we could all go together for a change.
Saki: We could also go to a cafe, check out clothing stores, a karaoke place...
Shiho: Is that the main reason you want to go?
Saki: Um... Those are just some other fun things we could do...
Saki: Hona...! Shiho's being mean to me...
Honami: There, there. No need to get upset.
Miku: Are you not interested in going to the observatory, Shiho?
Shiho: It's not that. I just think it's not worth the trip is all.
Shiho: That time would be better spent on more band practice.
Ichika: You're so down to earth, Shiho. Or down to play bass, I suppose.
Shiho: Is that supposed to be funny?
Ichika: Isn't it?
Saki: Sometimes the things you come out with are kind of bizarre, Ichi!
Ichika: Bizarre...
Honami: Saki, don't add fuel to the fire!
Shiho: If you just want to hang out, we can do that close to our station. There's no need to—
Luka: It's important to be in sync with each other if you're going to make good music as a team.
Shiho: Huh?
Luka: It's important to connect through things other than music every now and then. It can only help you as a band.
Miku: Yup, I agree.
Saki: Shiho... You really don't want to go?
Shiho: Sigh... Give me a moment to think it over.
Shiho: I have work on that day, so I'll have to swap my shift with someone else.
Saki: So you'll come? Yay!!
Shiho: Stop being so clingy. I get enough of that from my sister...
Miku: Sounds like you've persuaded her, Luka.
Luka: I only gave Shiho a little nudge in the direction she was already leaning towards.
Shiho: There's just one condition. Don't start slacking off with band practice because of this trip.
Shiho: If I see you start to get lazy, I'm out. Got it?
Saki: No worries! I'll practice diligently every day!
Honami: Every day? But you also have soft tennis club and your part-time job... Won't that be too much?
Saki: I'll be fine! I'm not how I used to be!
Ichika: You say that now, but you caught a bad cold that kept you in bed for a whole week after pushing yourself too hard that one time.
Saki: I can manage! Stop worrying so much, you two!
Saki: Nothing's going to stop me from enjoying my wonderful teenage life♪
Shiho: Yeah, of course.
Honami: Let's have a wonderful time, Saki!
Saki: Yeah!
Shiho: Is something the matter, Luka?
Luka: No, not really. It's nothing, really.
Miku: That only makes me more curious. What is it?
Luka: It's just that... Saki seemed a little different today.
Shiho: Oh?
Luka: The tone of her voice told me that she was straining herself.
Shiho: Her voice sounded strained...?
Shiho: That means... I don't want that to happen again...
Shiho: Thank you, Luka. I'll make sure to look after Saki.
Luka: Please do.
Saki: Shiho, let's get started with band practice!
Shiho: Alright. Saki, it's good to be enthusiastic, but don't push yourself past your limits, okay?
Saki: Hey, I'm not a little kid or anything...
Saki: I can play our songs perfectly now, you know!
Shiho: Really? Okay, let's make a bet. If you make a mistake, you've got to buy me ramen.
Saki: Whaaat?!
Shiho: It shouldn't be a problem if you're so confident, right? And if you play everything without slipping up, I'll treat you to bubble tea. Toppings and all, so it's a level price.
Saki: Your treat? I'm going to win this bet for sure!
Honami: Wait...!
Ichika: A-Are you okay, Honami?
Honami: When you think about it, it makes no sense! Why on earth does ramen cost the same as bubble tea?
Honami: When you think of the cost of the ingredients, it just doesn't add up... Right?
Ichika: Honami...
Shiho: You started shouting all of a sudden and we thought...
Honami: Oh? I-I'm sorry! It just hit me and...!
Saki: Hahaha! You made us all jump!
Honami: Sorry! L-Let's start practicing!
Saki: Okay! Let's start from just before the chorus. Get ready!
Miku: They seem to be having fun... Are you still worried, Luka?
Luka: A little.
Luka: Maybe I'm overthinking it...
